      "info": {
        "contact": {
          "name": "USPTO Open Data Portal",
          "url": "https://developer.uspto.gov/api-catalog"
        },
        "description": "The USPTO API Catalog provides developers with access to various APIs related to intellectual property. It includes information about registering, searching, and managing patents and trademarks, allowing for easy integration of government data into applications.",
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "USPTO Production Server",
            "url": "https://developer.uspto.gov"
          }
        ],
        "termsOfService": "https://www.uspto.gov/terms-use",
        "title": "USPTO API Catalog",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Search and retrieve US Patent and Trademark Office intellectual property data",
        "homepage": "https://developer.uspto.gov",
        "docs_url": "https://developer.uspto.gov",
        "license_short": "U.S. Government public data; works of the federal government are generally not subject to copyright in the United States.",
        "license_md": "- Data is produced by the United States Patent and Trademark Office, a U.S. federal agency.\n- U.S. federal government works are generally in the public domain within the United States (17 U.S.C. § 105).\n- No explicit licence or attribution text is published on the catalogue landing page; check the individual API documentation for terms before redistribution.\n- CORS is reported as disabled on the catalogue endpoint, so browser-only clients may need a proxy.",
        "about_md": "The USPTO API Catalog is a developer entry point published by the [United States Patent and Trademark Office](https://www.uspto.gov/), the federal agency that grants U.S. patents and registers trademarks. The catalogue surfaces machine-readable access to USPTO intellectual-property datasets through the [developer.uspto.gov](https://developer.uspto.gov) hub (which redirects to [data.uspto.gov](https://data.uspto.gov)).\n\nWhat you can do with the catalogue:\n\n- Query the intellectual-property marketplace dataset by free-text search (for example `searchText=vehicles`).\n- Discover other USPTO APIs covering patents and trademarks from a single index.\n- Pull government-sourced IP data for analytics, prior-art tooling, and brand-monitoring use cases.\n\nOperational notes: the catalogue endpoint exposes GET requests over HTTPS and does not document an API-key requirement on the landing page. CORS is disabled, so calls typically need to come from a server. Response times observed by third-party monitors averaged around 800 ms. Rate limits, auth schemes, and field-level licence terms vary per underlying API and should be confirmed in each API's own documentation.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "patent": "U.S. patent records and related intellectual-property marketplace data exposed through USPTO patent APIs reachable from the catalogue.",
          "trademark": "U.S. trademark filings and registrations accessible via the USPTO trademark APIs linked from the catalogue."
        },
        "auth": false
      },
